article.headline: Northeastern 89, Georgia St 63
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Jose Juan Barea had 26 points and 10 assists and Bennet Davis added 16 points as Northeastern ended a four-game losing streak with an 89-63 win over Georgia State on Thursday night. Barea made his first five shots and had 18 points and five assists as the Huskies (7-5, 3-1 Colonial) shot 55 percent from the field and outscored the Panthers in the paint 42-26 for their first victory since Dec. 7. Shawn James had seven points, eight rebounds and four blocks for Northeastern, which out-rebounded Georgia State 43-29. Justin Billingslea scored eight of his 14 points in the first half as the Panthers (3-8, 1-3) jumped to a 27-21 lead. Barea and James each had five points during a 14-0 run late in the first half as the Huskies pulled ahead 39-30. The Huskies took the lead for good when Barea found Janon Cole open for a layup that made it 32-30 with 5:40 left in the half. Cole had eight rebounds and scored seven of his nine points in the first half. The Huskies led 43-38 at halftime but opened the second half on an 18-3 run. Boyd Copeland scored 16 points and Malcolm Manier added 13 for the Panthers, who have lost seven of eight.
